{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_6","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' .claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Active Plan — Codex-Managed-Agent Roadmap Execution\n\nPlan anchor: `ROADMAP.md`\nWorkspace: `/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent`\nMirror workspace: `/home/clashuser/hzh/work_bo/codex_manager/vscode-extension`\n\n## Mission\nExecute `ROADMAP.md` to completion through bounded codex-loop slices. Do not branch into unrelated ideas. After each slice, preserve stability, package the extension, sync the dev mirror, and record a new evolution note.\n\n## Milestone Status\n\n### Milestone 1 — Architecture Stabilization\nStatus: mostly complete\n\nCompleted:\n- thin `extension.js`\n- `src/panel.js` reduced toward orchestration\n- host modules split into `server`, `codex-link`, `commands`, `auto-continue`, `lifecycle`, `panel-view`, `state-sync`\n- webview template split into `board`, `insights`, `drawer`\n\nRemaining cleanup:\n- keep `panel.js` from regrowing\n- prefer new host/webview modules for future work\n\n### Milestone 2 — Board Interaction Quality\nStatus: complete\n\nTargets:\n- improve drag smoothness and drop reliability\n- finish resize behavior for all supported directions\n- define clear card-size semantics for `T / S / M / L`\n- keep `Needs Human` useful without blocking the board\n- ensure the board remains the single interactive layout surface\n\nCompleted in this milestone:\n- directional board resize now preserves anchored edges for north/west handles and persists the adjusted `col` / `row` / `cols` / `height`\n- board drop-preview clearing now resets correctly when the pointer leaves card and board boundaries\n- board density semantics now reserve preview text for `M / L`, keeping `S` as a title-plus-progress tier\n- `Needs Human` now auto-expands when urgent cards newly appear after an empty state, preventing hidden intervention work\n- collapsed `Needs Human` now keeps an urgent-count summary visible without reopening the compact dock\n- compact `Needs Human` cards no longer pulse like main-board intervention cards, reducing visual competition\n- board drag is now blocked when the gesture starts on card controls, reducing accidental layout edits\n- board drag-active feedback now appears immediately on dragstart instead of waiting for the first deferred indicator sync\n- board UI now spells out the `T / S / M / L` size ladder so density semantics are explicit instead of implicit\n\nExit review:\n- drag / resize and compact-surface behavior are now close to the Milestone 2 stability target\n- `Needs Human` no longer blocks the main board and remains visible in collapsed form\n- previous size-semantics gap is now addressed in board UI copy\n- exit confirmation complete: Milestone 2 now satisfies the roadmap exit criteria closely enough to move on\n\n### Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer\nStatus: complete\n\nTargets:\n- stabilize usage report generation\n- improve topic map / word cloud / weekly shift interaction\n- make guidance more actionable and durable\n\nAudit findings:\n- host-side insights fallback already reads a persisted usage report from `~/.codex/codex_managed_agent_usage_report.json`\n- webview UI state persists topic-driven navigation state through `vscode.setState()`\n- first bounded reliability gap: persisted `topicFocus` is not revalidated against current insights data or current threads after reload\n- host-side persisted-report fallback is sufficient for webview reload recovery; a second reload-survivable webview cache would be redundant right now\n\nCompleted in this milestone:\n- persisted `topicFocus` is now cleared on reload when current thread data no longer supports the saved insight navigation state\n- active-session insights rendering now reuses the last usable report payload when a transient refresh arrives empty\n- insights UI now explicitly discloses when it is showing persisted fallback data or an in-session cached report\n- insights disclosure now includes a freshness timestamp for persisted fallback data and in-session cached reports\n- persisted fallback insights now get explicit stale wording once the cached report is older than a simple 24-hour threshold\n- topic-map-driven thread filtering now exposes an explicit clear-focus action directly in the thread summary surface\n- active `topicFocus` now highlights the matching topic-map node so the filtered target stays visually legible\n- weekly report now includes one concise next-action cue derived from the strongest weekly shift when available\n\nExit review:\n- current insights persistence/disclosure flow now covers reload fallback, in-session cache reuse, source disclosure, freshness disclosure, and stale wording\n- topic-map/thread-list linkage now covers click-to-filter, reload-safe focus validation, explicit clear-focus, and active-node highlighting\n- weekly report now includes one concise next-action cue, satisfying the remaining actionability gap closely enough for this milestone\n- exit confirmation complete: Milestone 3 now satisfies the roadmap exit criteria closely enough to move on\n\n### Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability\nStatus: active\n\nTargets:\n- background continue observability\n- clear loop status semantics\n- degraded-state handling\n- linked-vs-running distinction across surfaces\n\nAudit findings:\n- host-side auto-continue state already records `armed / queued / running / failed / success`, plus the last log path and last result detail\n- detailed loop state is currently visible inside larger board cards, but not in the compact thread-list scanning surface\n- first bounded reliability gap: users cannot quickly scan which threads have an armed, queued, running, or failed auto-loop without opening richer card UI\n- current visibility controls are split across low-level `Open Codex`, `Sidebar Codex`, `Archive`, `Unarchive`, and `Rename` actions instead of a roadmap-level `Show in Codex / Hide from Codex` path\n- first practical visibility-control gap is missing explicit `Show in Codex`: host primitives already support rename, unarchive, and Codex open, but the drawer does not yet bundle them into one intentional action\n\nExit review:\n- thread rows now expose compact loop state, while larger board cards still retain the richer log/result detail path\n- this is enough to satisfy the immediate loop-status scanning gap without changing host-side detached resume behavior\n- explorer grouping now gives `linked` threads a dedicated bucket instead of folding them into generic idle\n- spotlight now exposes a compact auto-loop log action, so log access is no longer confined to larger board cards\n- degraded-state recovery now exposes a direct service-log action instead of plain log-path text\n- spotlight now exposes the compact auto-loop state directly, which is sufficient for this inspector-level status gap\n- visibility-control audit complete: the missing piece is not another host primitive, but one explicit drawer-level `Show in Codex` action that can unarchive before opening the target thread in Codex\n- `Hide from Codex` can stay deferred one slice longer because existing `Archive` behavior already covers most of the hide path semantics\n\nCurrent bounded slice:\n- add one explicit `Show in Codex` drawer action that unarchives before opening the target thread in Codex\n\n### Milestone 5 — Publishable Product Quality\nStatus: pending\n\nTargets:\n- release workflow\n- screenshots / notes / docs\n- smoke validation routine\n- repo structure clarity\n\n## Slice Rules\n- Each tick completes one bounded, verifiable slice only.\n- Always validate syntax and package builds after code changes.\n- Always sync export repo changes back to the mirror workspace when behavior changes.\n- Always append an evolution note in `.claude/plans/loloop/`.\n- Update this active plan when milestone focus changes.\n\n## Immediate Next Slice Queue\n1. Add one explicit `Show in Codex` drawer action that unarchives before opening the target thread in Codex\n2. Re-review visibility control after that single action lands\n3. Milestone 5 remains blocked behind Milestone 4\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
